data.text:
Like mother, like son: Liv Tyler and son Milo sport matching his-and-her outfits while shopping in New York

She's a glamorous Hollywood star and the face of French fashion house Givenchy, but Liv Tyler's latest look is perhaps a little closer to home.

The 36 year-old performer, whose acting credits include Armageddon and Lord of the Rings, was seen wearing the same outfit as her eight year-old son, Milo, in New York yesterday.

Liv, the daughter of Aerosmith frontman Steven Tyler, wore a navy blue and white striped top with jeans and trainers. She teamed the look with over-sized sunglasses and a flash of red lipstick.

Perfect match: Liv Tyler and Milo step out in New York's West Village for some shopping

Retail therapy: The mother-of-one kept it casual while she shopped for essential in Manhattan

Meanwhile, her son copied the maritime theme, but swapped the blue denim for a pair of New York Knicks sweat pants.

The pair were seen shopping in Manhattan's West Village, where they strolled side-by-side to the delight of onlookers.

Yet, despite not purchasing much, they both looked content with their casual day out.

Don't want to miss a thing: Liv always enjoys spending time her her eight year-old son

Previously, Liv has spoken about the importance of her relationship with the eight year-old boy.
